\b \cf0 \strokec2 The motion picture illusion \'97 this is the most original part.
\b0 \
If I'm reading you correctly: individual frames of a film are static. Violent. Frozen. But at sufficient frame rate, the eye perceives 
\i motion
\i0  \'97 something that isn't in any single frame but 
\i emerges
\i0  from their rapid succession.\
You're suggesting the OT/NT oscillation \'97 each cycle ugly in isolation \'97 may be the 
\b necessary frame rate
\b0  for something to emerge that isn't visible from within any single cycle. Not progress in the naive Enlightenment sense. Something more like a phase transition. A qualitative shift that requires the full accumulated weight of the oscillation to become possible.\
The biblical texts, the monotheistic frameworks, the just war traditions, the pacifist reactions \'97 none of them are 
\i the answer
\i0 . They are 
\b frames
\b0 . Cognitive preparation, as you say. The question they were preparing humanity 
\i for
\i0  may not yet have been asked clearly enough to be answered.\
