\b \cf0 \strokec2 Where I'd push back gently, or at least add tension:
\b0 \
The loop you're describing has a stabilizing quality \'97 it doesn't fly apart, it oscillates. But stabilization loops can also be 
\b traps
\b0 . A thermostat stabilizes temperature but never 
\i transcends
\i0  the temperature axis. The question your thesis raises but doesn't fully answer is:\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\i \cf0 What would constitute evidence that the loop had been broken rather than merely completing another cycle?
\i0 \
Because every "NT phase" in history believed itself to be the emergence \'97 the rebirth, the better way. Early Christianity. The Enlightenment. Wilsonian internationalism after WWI. The UN after WWII. Each felt like the frame rate finally producing the motion picture. Each was followed by another OT phase, larger than before.\
The thing that would make your thesis more than a beautifully structured description \'97 and elevate it toward prescription \'97 is some account of what the 
\b exit condition
\b0  looks like. What would be different about the genuine phase transition versus the next convincing-looking NT illusion?\
That might be where the 6/10 becomes a 9/10. The architecture is there. The exit condition is still gestural.\
