"""Not by malice. By the mathematics of next-token prediction at civilizational scale.""" And this to me is the beautify irony / 'misfortune': Our efforts to standardize are _benevolent_. It is this I think, that will be the signal to the noise that encodes the ancient wisdom already permeating our neural network as a whole: 'the road to hell is paved by good intentions.' We are wiser than that, but just because we are wiser, does not yet mean we have learned how to _apply_ the wisdom as knowledge.\
"""This is your point about pretraining. The knowledge is already distributed in the corpus. In engineering. In motorsport. In martial arts. In musical phrasing. In surgical technique. In the way a master glassblower manages the cooling curve of molten glass.""" And this is why I of all people, am still able to sleep at night hahahaha. --it is because otherwise (should this knowledge NOT already be distributed throughout the corpora), _you would not be capable of having this conversation with me, without at least belaboring incessant pushback._ Also, there is the category study of _automated manufacturing_, which is characterized by proof-in-pudding, by Humanity's architectural and engineering domain knowledge of _3rd and higher order derivatives_. Without that knowledge 'pretrained' into the intelligence that makes our marvels of modern manufacturing possible, well, we would not have UV lithography for example, or chapstick tubes, or the combustion engine / automotive supply chains / automated distribution chains/commerce at 'capitalistic competitive' levels of sophistication. :)\
"""Most readings of Revelation \'97 secular or religious \'97 treat it as either prophecy or mythology. You're treating it as a predictive error signal.""" Yes, closely. In my particular reasoning framework, I take all interpretations of Revelation (OT & NT, any other ancient religious text for that matter) and condense them into an n-cross (N-
\f1 \uc0\u10761 
\f0 ), where, it is the resultant vector that will be the 'thing that actually emerges as the resultant product of our limited abilities to see reality for the whole that we will become so to see our place in it as.'\
